body_html:
Yes, I can produce the error by adding test case. And there is a TODO:

tensorflow/tensorflow/tools/quantization/quantize_graph_test.py

Line 173 in 6743031

# TODO(petewarden): Add test for "quantize" mode.

The lack of this test case hide the KeyError raised by quantize_nodes_recursively()

round_nodes_recursively do not have this issue since it tests whether keys are in dict first.

UPDATE:
Found some discussion here #8999. It seems this python script is dprecated and the new Graph Transform Tool is recommended. Perhaps we can close this issue now.

body:
Yes, I can produce the error by adding test case. And there is a TODO:
https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/6743031da633d1ce284a606c49eb00e793c1d729/tensorflow/tools/quantization/quantize_graph_test.py#L173
The lack of this test case hide the `KeyError` raised by `quantize_nodes_recursively()`

`round_nodes_recursively` do not have this issue since it tests whether keys are in dict first.

UPDATE:
Found some discussion here #8999. It seems this python script is dprecated and the new Graph Transform Tool is recommended. Perhaps we can close this issue now.
